About us

Fozzy Group is one of the largest trade industrial groups in Ukraine and one of the leading Ukrainian retailers, with over 700 outlets all around the country. It is also engaged in e-commerce, food processing & production, agricultural business, parcel delivery, logistics and banking.

Since its inception in 1997, Fozzy Group has focused on making innovative business improvements, creating new opportunities for the market, and further developing the industry as a whole.

Job Description:

Silpo E-Commerce Analytics Tribe is looking for Data Analyst to help us with the implementation of the advanced analytical systems for the rapid growth of the food delivery business. We are expanding our Data Analytics capabilities across multiple domains — Marketing, Product, Commercial, and Operational. As a Data Analyst, you can join a dedicated analytics team supporting one of those domains:

Operational Analytics — empowering food delivery operations with real-time insights and performance tracking, building optimization solutions to improve operational efficiency;

Product & Marketing Analytics — optimizing digital product performance, user behavior, campaign effectiveness, customer acquisition, and churn prevention;

Commercial Analytics — supporting assortment strategy, pricing optimization, and promotional performance analysis.

You can choose your preferred area of work or be assigned to a team based on your expertise and background.

Job Responsibilities

Analyze data on products, services, and business functions to forecast performance, provide actionable insights and recommendations for product management and business growth;

Extensively utilize SQL and dbt (Data Build Tool) to design, develop, and optimize data models within our high-volume data platform, effectively managing and processing multi-billion-row datasets.

Develop professional dashboards and define key metrics;

Conduct A/B tests to identify hidden effects on food delivery consumer behavior, growth drivers & profitability metrics;

Create reports and presentations for top & senior management;

Work closely with Business Stakeholders, Product Owners, Business Analysts, and Data Engineers throughout the entire project lifecycle.

Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Mathematics / Quantitative Economics / Econometrics / Statistics / Computer Sciences / Finance;

At least 2 years of working experience in Data & Analytics roles;

Strong mathematical background in Statistics, Probability, Linear algebra, and Optimization Techniques;

Experience in writing advanced SQL queries, handling structured and unstructured data, data wrangling, data visualization, and predictive modeling;

Understanding of data warehousing concepts and data modeling techniques;

Willingness to learn, curiosity, professionalism, dedication, and ability to work under pressure in a fast-paced environment.

Skills

Must Have

Proficiency with BI Tools (Power BI, Looker, Tableau)

SQL (Window & Analytic functions, Nested Queries);

Skills in Advanced Regression Modeling, Multivariate Analysis, Time Series Analysis, and application of Statistical Concepts (Hypothesis testing, A/B tests, Factor analysis / PCA).

Preferred

Python (at least numpy, pandas, sklearn);

